{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"certifiable":true,"findings":[{"citations":[{"description":"rollback_recovery test only tests reduce_ticket re-inference, not fsck detection or repair","kind":"file","line_end":171,"line_start":154,"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py"},{"description":"SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL detection code exists in production but is untested","kind":"file","line_end":321,"line_start":303,"path":"src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py"},{"description":"Repair routing for SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL exists in production but is untested","kind":"file","line_end":220,"line_start":206,"path":"src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py"}],"criterion":"rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log plus conservative-horizon compaction preserve the same provenance while later live events replay normally. A simulated old-style SNAPSHOT missing creation_channel is detected and repaired from its retained CREATE through the existing fsck --repair-snapshots seam. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery\" && uv run pytest -q tests/integration/test_concurrency_regression.py.","detail":"The 'rebuild' and 'horizon' sub-criteria are covered by `test_rebuild_snapshot_preserves_creation_channel` and `test_horizon_compaction_preserves_creation_channel`. However, the 'rollback_recovery' test (`test_rollback_recovery_reinfers_legacy_snapshot_channel`, lines 155–171) only verifies read-time re-inference: it strips `creation_channel` from a compacted SNAPSHOT's `compiled_state` and asserts that `reduce_ticket` re-infers `jira`+`inferred` at restore time. It does NOT exercise the fsck `SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL` detection path (fsck.py lines 303–321) nor the `--repair-snapshots` route through `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` (fsck.py lines 206–220). No test anywhere searches for or asserts `SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL` in fsck output (search for `SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL` in tests/ returns zero hits). The criterion requires that a stale snapshot is DETECTED (fsck surfaces `SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL`) AND REPAIRED (fsck --repair-snapshots rebuilds it from the retained CREATE) — the test covers only the read-time fallback half of that obligation.","dimension":"completion","remediation":"Add a test (e.g. in test_creation_channel_compaction.py under a name matching `rollback_recovery`) that: (1) compacts a legacy Jira ticket so a SNAPSHOT exists and the CREATE is retired, (2) strips creation_channel from the SNAPSHOT's compiled_state to simulate the old-code-compaction scenario, (3) calls fsck_cli([]) and asserts 'SNAPSHOT_STALE_CHANNEL' appears in the output, (4) calls fsck_cli(['--repair-snapshots']) and asserts rc==0, and (5) verifies that the rebuilt SNAPSHOT's compiled_state now carries creation_channel='jira' and creation_channel_inferred=True.","reviewer_id":"completion-verifier","severity":"high"}],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","remediation":"How to resolve the unmet criteria: for each one, decide whether the work is genuinely incomplete or simply undocumented. If a requirement is already satisfied but the proof is not discoverable from the code alone, add a comment to this ticket that documents the evidence — cite the concrete artifacts that meet the requirement (file paths and line ranges, commands and their output, links, or the reasoning that ties the work to the criterion). The completion verifier reads this ticket's comments, so evidence you record there is taken into account on the next verification. For any criterion whose work is genuinely unfinished, complete it, then re-verify.","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_fail_v1","ticket_id":"568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87","verdict":"FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784287945216972001,"uuid":"b3fb0b03-e4f3-4f12-a8d8-b26d5c2de212"}